A few areas in Pietermaritzburg are expected to have a power outage due to the maintenance of the Mayors Walk exchange substation on Tuesday and Wednesday. The Msunduzi electricity department released a statement warning residents of the outage. The affected areas include Prestbury, Clarendon, Tomlison, Signal Hill, Mpumuza, Boughton and parts of Brackridge. According to the statement, the estimated duration is 8 hours. “The maintenance is scheduled to start on Tuesday from 8am- 4pm and again on Wednesday from 8am-4pm,” read the statement. The department has urged all consumers to always treat all electrical equipment and installations as live. “We regret any inconvenience that may be experienced during this period,” read the statement.